Bullet's DrawDebugGeometry() function when drawing convex shapes draws convex vertices in un-ordered fashion (left).  
![drawconvex](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/14249868/28389048-7afe3ffe-6c89-11e7-91be-d51d1f668e69.jpg)

Here's a CollisionShape::DrawDebugConvexShape() helper function which draws the shape properly (right).

```
void CollisionShape::DrawDebugConvexShape(DebugRenderer* dbgRenderer, bool depthTest)
{
    if (GetShapeType() == SHAPE_CONVEXHULL)
    {
        ConvexData *convxData = (ConvexData*)GetGeometryData();
        Matrix3x4 worldTransform = node_->GetWorldTransform();
        RigidBody* body = GetComponent<RigidBody>();
        Color color(Color::GREEN);

        if (body)
        {
            if (body->IsActive())
            {
                color = Color::WHITE;
            }
            worldTransform = Matrix3x4(body->GetPosition(), body->GetRotation(), node_->GetWorldScale());
        }
        for (unsigned i = 0; i < convxData->indexCount_; i += 3)
        {
            Vector3 a = worldTransform * convxData->vertexData_[convxData->indexData_[i + 0]];
            Vector3 b = worldTransform * convxData->vertexData_[convxData->indexData_[i + 1]];
            Vector3 c = worldTransform * convxData->vertexData_[convxData->indexData_[i + 2]];
            dbgRenderer->AddLine(a, b, color, depthTest);
            dbgRenderer->AddLine(b, c, color, depthTest);
            dbgRenderer->AddLine(a, c, color, depthTest);
        }
    }
}



```

There used to be one in the Terrain class which returned incorrect values then eventually removed. I'd like to submit this:

```
Vector3 Terrain::HeightMapToWorld(const IntVector2& pixelPosition) const
{
    if (!node_)
        return Vector3::ZERO;

    IntVector2 pos(pixelPosition.x_, numVertices_.y_ - 1 - pixelPosition.y_);
    float xPos = (float)(pos.x_ * spacing_.x_ + patchWorldOrigin_.x_);
    float zPos = (float)(pos.y_ * spacing_.z_ + patchWorldOrigin_.y_);
    Vector3 Lpos(xPos, 0.0f, zPos);
    Vector3 WPos = node_->GetWorldTransform() * Lpos;
    WPos.y_ = GetHeight(WPos);

    return WPos;
}

```

I have multiple similar nodes to animate. Basic event subscriptions are insufficient to know which nodes finish. There are no senders in the callback or in the `VariantMap& eventData`. I can only think of two workaround

1. Use eventTypes as the animation IDs and store them in a `map`
2. Use `std::bind`
```
SharedPtr<ValueAnimation> animation(new ValueAnimation(GetContext()));
animation->SetEventFrame(duration, StringHash(1));
node->SetAttributeAnimation("Position", animation, WM_ONCE);
SubscribeToEvent(node, StringHash(1), bind(&MyClass::MyCallback, this, SharedPtr<Node>(node), _1, _2));
```

Is there a built-in way to do it ~~(without subclassing `Node`)~~?
